               <p>
Wed: Jany. 4th    a Cold Clear morning, the river Covered with Ice from the <name type="place" key="Missouri River">Missouri</name>, the <name type="place" key="Mississippi River">Massissippi</name> above frosed across, the Wind from the West, The Thermometer this morning at 19° below freesing [<hi rend="italic">13° F.</hi>], Continue Cold &amp; Clear all day, I took the altd. of S. [sun's] L. L and found it to be 57° 27' 15" N, purchase 12 lb Tallow for 6/—of <name type="person" key="Whiteside, William">Whitesides</name>, who Sold the Beef to the Com; [commissary] at 3$ pr. Hw [hundredweight]    Several Countrey people here to day—    at 4 oClock the murcuria of the Thmtr. in a corner of a warm room was 20 D. above (0)—</p>
               <p>
                  <name type="person" key="Werner, William">Worner</name> &amp; <name type="person" key="Potts, John">Potts</name> fight after Dark without my Knowledge &amp; the Corpl.<ref target="n03010401" n="1"/> head of the mess left the hut &amp; Suffered them to bruse themselves much, he has no authority, the other Part of the detachment verry merry at night</p>
